{
  "text": "Lemma 2 can be explained as follows. An increase in the environmental tax on the firm increases the price of the consumption good, leading to a decrease in consumption, hence \u2202q t \u03c4 /\u2202t < 0. As a decrease in consumption resulting from an increase in the environmental tax does not change the marginal benefit of waste reduction effort, waste reduction effort is not affected, hence \u2202e t \u03c4 /\u2202t = 0. An increase in the waste collection charge increases the marginal cost of consumption, as an additional unit of waste from consumption has to be disposed of at higher cost, [CITATION_1] hence \u2202q t \u03c4 /\u2202\u03c4 < 0. Finally, an increase in the waste collection charge increases the waste reduction effort, as it increases the marginal benefit of such effort; hence \u2202e t \u03c4 /\u2202\u03c4 > 0.",
  "citation_candidates": [
